I observe kids to be highly skilled in having fun compared with adults.
It makes me suspect if adults have anything at all to offer children.
Adults manipulate children to produce more adults, or in other words, adults
deprive children of their ability to have fun, and call it 'maturing.'
Do you not see this to be the case?
I see a little toddler skipping along in the rain, the somber parent following.
